Aquatic Spell							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Metamagic																																																																																																	DESC:You can cast your spells under or into water.																														ADDSPELLLEVEL:1																				SOURCEPAGE:p.14									BENEFIT:An aquatic spell functions normally when underwater and requires no caster level check to cast, even if it possesses the fire descriptor. In addition, the spell can be cast from the surface into water and still be effective. An aquatic spell uses up a spell slot 1 level higher than the spell's actual level.
Armored Athlete							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																													PREMULT:1,[PREPROFWITHARMOR:1,TYPE.Medium],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Armor Proficiency (Medium)]							PRESKILL:1,TYPE.Dexterity=3,TYPE.Strength=3						PRETEXT:Light armor proficiency, medium armor proficiency, 3 ranks in any Dexterity- or Strength-based skill.															DESC:You have experience using a skill while armored.											STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SKILL|TYPE=Charisma|TYPE=Dexterity|TYPE=Intelligence|TYPE=Strength|TYPE=Wisdom																							SOURCEPAGE:p.9	ASPECT:Ability Benefit|Armored Athlete - %LIST	BENEFIT:Choose one Dexterity- or Strength-based skill in which you possess at least 3 ranks. When you attempt a check for the chosen skill, your armor check penalty on that check for wearing light or medium armor is reduced by 3 (to a minimum of 0). If you have 10 or more ranks in the skill, the penalty is instead reduced by 6 (to a minimum of 0). If you have armor training 2 and are proficient with heavy armor, this benefit also applies to armor check penalties for wearing heavy armor. Special: You can gain this feat multiple times. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new skill.
Artful Dodge							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																													PREMULT:1,[PRESTAT:1,INT=13],[PREVARGTEQ:CombatFeatIntRequirement,13]																									PRETEXT:Int 13.																							DEFINE:FeatDexRequirement|0				DESC:You are practiced at avoiding attacks when outnumbered.																															SERVESAS:ABILITY=FEAT|Dodge		BONUS:VAR|FeatDexRequirement|max(DEXSCORE,INTSCORE)|TYPE=Base			SOURCEPAGE:p.7									BENEFIT:If you are the only character threatening an opponent, you gain a +1 dodge bonus to AC against that opponent. Special: The Artful Dodge feat acts as the Dodge feat for the purpose of satisfying prerequisites that require Dodge. You can use Intelligence, rather than Dexterity, for feats with a minimum Dexterity prerequisite.
Circling Mongoose							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Dodge,Mobility,Spring Attack																	PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,13],[PREVARGTEQ:FeatDexRequirement,13]																								PRETEXT:Dex 13, Dodge, Mobility, Spring Attack, base attack bonus +6.											PRETOTALAB:6									DESC:You keep your opponent on the defensive as you circle around threateningly.																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.7									BENEFIT:When adjacent to a foe, as a full-round action, you can take a full-attack action to make melee attacks against the foe, moving 5 feet before each attack. You must move 5 feet before each melee attack you make, and can't exceed your maximum speed, maximum number of attacks in a round, or attack any other target until the beginning of your next turn. You must remain adjacent to the foe, and your movement provokes attacks of opportunity as normal. If your first attack hits, you are considered to be flanking the foe on your second attack. Subsequent attacks made as part of the full-attack action continue to be treated as if you were flanking the foe until one misses, at which point your attacks are treated normally.
Deadly Grappler							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Grapple,Improved Unarmed Strike															PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,13],[PREVARGTEQ:FeatDexRequirement,13]																								PRETEXT:Dex 13, Improved Grapple, Improved Unarmed Strike.																								DESC:While you're grappled, you become even more dangerous.																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.14									BENEFIT:You have learned to leverage a grappling creature's weight against it. While you're grappled, attacks you make against the grappler using armor spikes, a light or one-handed weapon, a natural weapon, or an unarmed strike deal damage as if the strike or weapon were one size category larger than it actually is.
Explosive Escape							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat			PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Grapple,Improved Unarmed Strike															PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,13],[PREVARGTEQ:FeatDexRequirement,13]																				PRESTAT:1,STR=13		PRETEXT:Dex 13, Str 13, Improved Grapple, Improved Unarmed Strike.																						DESC:When you break a grapple, you can send your assailants flying away from you.																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.14									BENEFIT:When you succeed at a combat maneuver check to break a grapple, you can choose to throw back any enemies participating in the grapple who are up to one size category larger than you. Such foes are thrown 5 feet directly away from you and take an amount of nonlethal damage equal to that of your unarmed attack.
