Cudgeler Sweep							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat,Style		PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Bludgeoner,Cudgeler Style																		PREMULT:1,[PRETOTALAB:5],[PREVARGTEQ:MonkFeatQualify,5]																											PRETEXT:Bludgeoner, Cudgeler Style, base attack bonus +5 or monk level 5th.																					DESC:Your powerful blows can knock down your opponents.																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.13									BENEFIT:When you hit with a charge attack using the Cudgeler Style feat, you can immediately attempt a single trip combat maneuver check against the target with a +2 competence bonus as a free action. This provokes an attack of opportunity as normal for a trip combat maneuver.
Cudgeler Takedown							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat,Style		PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Bludgeoner,Cudgeler Style,Cudgeler Sweep															PREMULT:1,[PRETOTALAB:9],[PREVARGTEQ:MonkFeatQualify,9]																											PRETEXT:Bludgeoner, Cudgeler Style, Cudgeler Sweep, base attack bonus +9 or monk level 9th.																		DESC:Opponents you batter to the ground stay down.																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.13									BENEFIT:When you hit with a charge attack using the Cudgeler Style feat, your weapon deals damage as though it were one size category larger for 1 round or until it leaves your hand. When you successfully trip an opponent with the Cudgeler Sweep feat, your opponent must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC %1) or be stunned for 1 round.|10+floor(TL/2)+STR
Kraken Style							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat,Style		PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Grapple,Improved Unarmed Strike															PREMULT:1,[PRETOTALAB:3],[PREVARGTEQ:MonkFeatQualify,3]																							PRESTAT:1,WIS=13		PRETEXT:Wis 13, Improved Grapple, Improved Unarmed Strike, base attack bonus +3 or monk level 3rd.																	DESC:You savagely squeeze and twist when grappling.																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.13									BENEFIT:When you succeed at a grapple check while using this style, your opponent takes %1 points of bludgeoning damage in addition to any damage your grapple deals, such as when you choose to harm your opponent as part of a successful check to maintain a grapple. In addition, you gain a +2 bonus on combat maneuver checks to maintain a grapple.|WIS
Kraken Throttle							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat,Style		PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Grapple,Improved Unarmed Strike,Kraken Style													PREMULT:1,[PRETOTALAB:5],[PREVARGTEQ:MonkFeatQualify,5]																							PRESTAT:1,WIS=13		PRETEXT:Wis 13, Improved Grapple, Improved Unarmed Strike, Kraken Style, base attack bonus +5 or monk level 5th.															DESC:You tighten your grip around your target's throat.																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.13									BENEFIT:The damage that you deal with the Kraken Style feat on a successful grapple combat maneuver check increases to %1. While using this style, you can choke your opponent when you successfully maintain a grapple instead of choosing to damage, move, pin, or tie up your opponent. This suffocates your opponent (CRB p.445). The grappled opponent can take a breath during any round in which you do not maintain the grapple.|WIS+2
Kraken Wrack							CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat,Style		PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Improved Grapple,Improved Unarmed Strike,Kraken Throttle													PREMULT:1,[PRETOTALAB:7],[PREVARGTEQ:MonkFeatQualify,7]																							PRESTAT:1,WIS=13		PRETEXT:Wis 13, Improved Grapple, Improved Unarmed Strike, Kraken Style, Kraken Throttle, base attack bonus +7 or monk level 7th.												DESC:You squeeze your opponent tightly enough to crush armor or items between you.																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.13									BENEFIT:The damage you deal with the Kraken Style feat on a successful grapple combat maneuver check increases to %1. While using this style, you can crush your opponent when you successfully maintain a grapple instead of choking, damaging, moving, pinning, or tying up your opponent. When you do, you deal an amount of damage equal to that of your unarmed strike or one of your natural attacks to your foe's armor or an item held in your foe's hand. This crushing damage bypasses half of the hardness of the armor or item.|WIS+4

